      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Fresh Spin</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mort Rubinstein letter holds Bernard Holland's July 2 article neglects to mention Hyperion, Naxos, ECM, CPO and other copanes that are recording little-known composers and putting fresh spin on traditional ones (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bernard Holland criticizes the classical record industry and review business for lack of innovation. He neglects to mention enterprising companies such as Hyperion, Naxos, ECM, CPO et al., which are recording little-known composers and putting a fresh spin on traditional ones. His reluctance to listen to multiple recordings of the same music perhaps tells more about his own habits than the general state of the industry today.</p>
        <p>MORT RUBINSTEIN  Syosset, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bernard Holland criticizes the classical record industry and review business for lack of innovation. He neglects to mention enterprising companies such as Hyperion, Naxos, ECM, CPO et al., which are recording little-known composers and putting a fresh spin on traditional ones. His reluctance to listen to multiple recordings of the same music perhaps tells more about his own habits than the general state of the industry today.</p>
        <p>MORT RUBINSTEIN  Syosset, N.Y.</p>
        <p>CLASSICAL RECORDINGS</p>
      </block>
